16 WHEREAS, Dr. Cooper currently works at his practice, Cooper Pediatrics, PC, in Duluth,
17 Georgia, as well as serves as a Clinical Assistant Professor of Community Medicine at
18 Mercer University School of Medicine; and
19 WHEREAS, he has left an indelible mark on his community through health initiatives at
20 Graves Elementary School and Luck Shoals Park, where he not only provided staff and
21 equipment but also facilitated the distribution of vaccines; and
22 WHEREAS, he is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
23 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Dr. Jeffery D. Cooper of Cooper
28 Pediatrics for his efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of
29 Georgia and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Dr.
32 Jeffery D. Cooper.
